relation: Preschool Open House Location: Crossings Community Church, Sanford Fl Come check out Crossings Community Preschool! Our classrooms have been newly renovated and open for viewing. You will also be able to meet some of our staff! We will have a bounce house, crafts, popcorn, cookies and lemonade. This is one event you won’t want to miss! View Map & Details

Youth Explosion Location: Words of Encouragement, Orlando FLORIDA (FL) At youth explosion there will be games, free food and three gospel rap artists will be attending. There will be bounce houses, cotton candy and even clothes and shoes that were donated for the children. There will be prizes also available for children. Pastor Lloyd Redden and first lady Nicole Redden are holding the youth explosion for the saving of lives of our youth. Please call 321.460.3338 and speak to pastor Redden for more details. View Map & Details

Tim Serdynski Album Release w/ 7th Surrender and Sam Massaro Location: Music Go Round, Lakeland Fl FREE concert! Tim Serdynski Album Release w/ 7th Surrender & Sam Massaro (of Emberlasting) A limited # of physical CD’s will be available at this event, so be sure to get here as soon as possible! Digital release will occur on ALL major mp3 outlets the same day! For more information, visit the Tim Serdynski website! We look forward to seeing you here! View Map & Details

"In Honor of Your Majesty" - Choir Concert Location: USF School of Music Concert hall, Tampa Florida Choir Concert with an African flavor! This promises to be an evening of pure praise and celebration of music to the one most deserving of it. We hope you would join us as we move to bring God’s throne on earth! This event will feature original songs from the Victorious Voices, as well as many songs we have come to know and love in our unique African way. You do not want to be told about this. It is an experience to cherish! View Map & Details

Calvary's Light Concert Location: Orlando Central Church, Orlando FL Invite your friends and family to come with you to an evening of rich harmonies and uplifting music. Experience God’s love, hope and peace as you listen to the music they sing. ALL are welcome and the event is FREE! Calvary’s Light is a men’s musical ministry that was started by four young men from the Apopka area in 1999. They hope their music encourages you to seek a closer relationship with God. Calvary’s Light has recorded one CD titled His Peace Is Mine. There are many troubles facing us every day. God is the only place that everyone can turn to and find true peace because His Peace Is Mine. We hope to see you there! View Map & Details

BACK 2 SCHOOL BASH Location: St. Paul’s Church, Gotha FL St. Paul’s Church invites you and your family to their Back 2 School Bash, to celebrate the start of a new school year! There celebration will be prizes, special meals and guest speaker Dr. Angela Osbourne, Florida’s 2015 Principal of the Year, who will be sharing tips for a successful school year. Kids 3-years-old through 5th grade will enjoy bounce houses, games, snacks and fun. The event will be held at both of our church services at 9 a.m. and 11 a.m. We hope to see you there! View Map & Details

Back to School Bash and Free haircuts Location: Victory Church Orlando, altamonte springs fl Your invited to our back to school bash! We will be giving away back packs, school supplies and FREE haircuts along with having Jeremiah’s Italian ice! For more information visit, Victory Church Orlando; come out and be blessed! View Map & Details

End of Summer Bash and Ice Cream Party Location: St. Mark’s United Methodist Church, Indialantic Florida We’re excited to bring a member of the Strength Team to St. Mark’s for our End of Summer Bash! People of all ages will be inspired by the team member’s testimony of faith and amazing feats of strength. Following the presentation we will have a cool ice cream party and lots of giveaways! This is one summer bash you won’t want to miss! View Map & Details

Once Weekly Classes for Home-educated Students Location: Metro Life Church, Casselberry Florida The Regent Academy offers academic and elective classes for home educated students grades K-12 which begin on August 11, 2015 and continue for 32 weeks, ending May 3, 2016. We also offer many support services such as Stanford Achievement Tests, school portraits, encouragement for moms, and more! Classes are open to anyone in the community. We are not a school covering, and all classes are a la carte. Registration is currently open!! Please visit our website at The Regent Academy or contact Angie Mendez, angiemendez93@gmail.com for more information. View Map & Details

Better Breathers Club Location: Florida Hospital Celebration, Celebration FL Better Breathers Clubs offer the opportunity to learn ways to better cope with COPD while getting the support of others who share in your struggles. These support groups give you the tools you need to live the best quality of life you can. Meeting will be held at Palms Conference Room. Please contact Gina Siberon at 407.303.4057 for further information. Topics include: Breathing Techniques Medical Tests Home Health Care Lung Transplants View Map & Details
